Text: Fin måte å bli kvitt valkene etter juleribba. Takker !

I don't speak Swedish, so I used an online translation program and it came up with:

Delicate mte become get rid cushion etter juleribba. Takker!

I assume cushion is Swedish for beer-belly!

Hehe, i´ll give you a hint... Never use an Swedish translator when someone writes in Norwegian. 

Im not fluent speaking norwegian, but i´l try give you better translation, even though i dubt you have any good use for it. But its X-mas so here it comes:

"Fin måte å bli kvitt valkene etter juleribba. Takker "

"Nice need to get rid of the fat/"tires" after the x-mas ribs. Thanks"

Well I used a web based translator, and thought this is a Swedish site...

Tried again with Nowegian, and got:

Fine mte become get rid valkene after juleribba. thanking

Computer translations crack me up sometimes...  The Swedish translation was funnier though (although not as useless).
